# Project-local ChkTeX config for mentor-rl-methods.
# Auto-loaded by chktex from the working directory (and honored by the
# VS Code LaTeX Workshop linter, which runs chktex from the project root).
#
# We silence purely-stylistic warnings and a couple of false positives that
# are noise in this math-heavy proposal. Substantive warnings (unbalanced
# braces, bad math mode, missing ~ before \cite/\ref, etc.) stay ON.
#
# To re-enable any warning, delete its -n line. Reference:
#   1  Command terminated with space      -> algpseudocode \State etc. (style)
#   3  Enclose previous parenthesis {}     -> math nitpick (style)
#   9  ')' expected, found ']'             -> false positive from interval $(0,1]$
#   12 Interword spacing \  should be used -> abbreviation spacing (style)
#   13 Intersentence spacing \@            -> "vs.", "et al." spacing (style)
#   17 '(' count doesn't match ')'         -> false positive from interval $(0,1]$
#   24 Delete space (pageref correctness)  -> space before \label in floats (style)
#   38 Punctuation in front of quotes      -> "...?''" is correct here (style)

CmdLine
{
    -n1
    -n3
    -n9
    -n12
    -n13
    -n17
    -n24
    -n38
}
